race.comment: LINDOS (12) is a filly by Anders on debut for the Bateup stable. She's been impressive at the trials, trialling behind sharp 2YO Masvingo recently where she wasn't disgraced. Looks a good maiden, but she's shown plenty of talent and can make a statement on debut. VANTANTE (14) proved her run two back was no fluke when leading throughout at this track and trip last start, only being gunned down late. Can find the front again for Ramsbotham with the 1.5kg claim coming in handy. Trending the right way and will be tough to catch. TOP SPEED (5) disappointed at Nowra two back before a good run at Taree last time out. Drawn low again today and rates highly on his most recent run. PARIAH TIME (4) just missed on debut when behind VANTANTE and has to be included. KITTY OKAY (7) has trialled well coming into this and showed class in her debut campaign. Keep safe.
